The paper deals with graph coloring and approximation algorithms, which are topics commonly studied in computer science. The use of Vizing's theorem and the study of subgraphs suggest that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The study of graphs and their properties also suggests that the paper may belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the use of approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
